      "content": "oh okay i get it now. so it's basically these motor proteins and enzymes doing all the heavy lifting. it sounds like a lot of chaotic movement happening all at once inside the cell. is there any part of the process where things might get messy or where the cell has to deal with mistakes or errors in how everything is being pulled apart?",
